{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01PEZA3hsr2B9TReYRQHh3YD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me carefully compare the knowledge file against the source file to identify any issues.\n\n**V1: Omission Check**\n\nLet me go through the source file section by section:\n\nSource has these sections:\n1. アルファベット順 (A～G, H～N, O～U, V～Z)\n2. 五十音順 (あ行, か行, さ行, た行, な行, は行, ま行, や行, ら行, わ行)\n\nThe knowledge file has sections s1-s8, covering:\n- s1: アルファベット順 (A-G + H-N + V-Z combined)\n\n\n- s2-s8: あ行 through ら行\n\nNote that ま行, や行, わ行 are \"対象用語なし\" (no terms), so they're legitimately omitted. O～U is also empty in the source.\n\nNow I'm checking each entry carefully, starting with the alphabetical terms in s1. Looking at A-G entries from the source, I can see Action（業務アクションハンドラ）is present, and I need to verify the rest of the entries match up correctly.\n\nVerifying H-N and V-Z sections...\n\nThe automated pre-check flagged a section count mismatch: 8 sections versus 13 source headings. Let me recount the RST h2 and h3 headings in the source to understand where the discrepancy is coming from. I'm noticing the discrepancy between the 14 h3 headings in the source and the 8 sections in the knowledge file. Looking at which sections actually contain terms, I count 10 non-empty sections since four of them are marked as having no target terms. So the automated check flagging 8 < 13 makes sense, but the real gap is between the 10 sections with content and what's currently stored.\n\nThe merging of the alphabetical ranges (A-G, H-N, V-Z) into a single section seems reasonable since they're all part of the same alphabetical grouping. That consolidation from 10 down to 8 sections is justifiable given the structure.\n\nNow I'm checking the actual content of each section to verify the entries are accurate, starting with the コード管理 section. 次の部分では、コード管理機能の詳細を参照するよう指示されている。その後、ステレオタイプという用語の定義を確認していて、典型的なインターフェ